history.text: Hello
Hey
I really loved Keanu in this part, what about you?
Yes, he played the part well in my opinion.
I like that it had a lot of action.
Do you normally like Action movies?
Yes, do you?
What did you think about the storyline?
I do, they keep my attention really well. I loved how you didnt know what he was going to do next.
Yeah, the suspense kept me on the edge of my seat the entire time.
I feel like the critics just use big words, do you think they were right about their opinons?
I usually go by Rotten Tomatoes when looking for reviews.  I think they could of gone a little higher with the review.
Do you think John's boss should have left him go?
Yes, but it wouldn't of been as good, I think.
Do you like the director Chad Stahelski?
I never pay attention to director names honestly, so I cant name any other movies directed by him.
Same here, I never heard of him before.
I think the names of the characters fit the part.
I also like his name, its quick to say and catchy. I love that the guy was mean to his son because he knew what he did and knew he was in trouble.
I liked that he got punched and throws him out when he finds out who the car was stolen from John.
I love that his revenge is based on principal and not on just money or drugs, he is doing it for a reason close to himself.
Yes, I agree that is what makes it so good.

I love how none of the other assassins
 can get him, like why are yall trying, he is the best for a reason!
I love how he destroyed Viggo's money before he is captured.
Yeah that really showed him who was boss didnt it?
I love how John let Viggo get the upper hand, but it was just a trick so he could murder him.
Yes, and the fist fight at the dock was intense.   Then he was stabbed.
It is great and wonderful turnaround.
It really kinda of made you see how smart the character was and how dedicated he was to his cause.
I loved how he saved the puppy from death at the end.
It was a great segway for sure.
I love when movies have solid endings like this one did.
I wonder if being a pit bull puppy had any significance.
